{"questionId":"12269","questionHtml":"<p class=\"indent1\" style=\"margin-top:12pt;text-align:left;\">Find the values of the real number <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"k\">\n  <mi>k</mi>\n</math></span> for which the determinant of the matrix&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  {k - 4}&amp;3 \\\\   { - 2}&amp;{k + 1}  \\end{array}} \\right)\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mi>k</mi>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mn>4</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>3</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mn>2</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mi>k</mi>\n              <mo>+</mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> is equal to zero.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left| {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  {k - 4}&amp;3 \\\\   { - 2}&amp;{k + 1}  \\end{array}} \\right| = 0\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>|</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mi>k</mi>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mn>4</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>3</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mn>2</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mi>k</mi>\n              <mo>+</mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>|</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" \\Rightarrow \\left( {k - 4} \\right)\\left( {k + 1} \\right) + 6 = 0\">\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">⇒</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>k</mi>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>4</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>k</mi>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>6</mn>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" \\Rightarrow {k^2} - 3k + 2 = 0\">\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">⇒</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>k</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>3</mn>\n  <mi>k</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" \\Rightarrow \\left( {k - 2} \\right)\\left( {k - 1} \\right) = 0\">\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">⇒</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>k</mi>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>k</mi>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" \\Rightarrow k = 2\">\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">⇒</mo>\n  <mi>k</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n</math></span> or&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"k = 1\">\n  <mi>k</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)&nbsp; (C3)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"12269","referenceCode":"EXM.1.AHL.TZ0.44","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the values of the real number k for which the determinant of the matrix ( k − 4 3 − 2 k + 1 ) is equal to zero.","paper":"1","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"44","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.14—Introduction to matrices"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}